# jobhound_core Development Guidelines

Spec-driven workflow via `.specify` and `/speckit.*` commands. Update this file when plans change (or run the Specify update script when wired).

## Active Technologies

- Go 1.24 ‚Äî standard library first; `net/http` / `html` / `encoding/json` for Tier-1 API and static fetchers
- `github.com/PuerkitoBio/goquery` for HTML sources (Tier 2)
- `github.com/go-rod/rod` + session cookies file for LinkedIn (Tier 3)
- PostgreSQL + GORM + migrations ‚Äî jobs, history, profile, dedup
- Temporal ‚Äî workflows/activities for manual runs and scheduled events
- Claude API for scoring; product delivery channels (e.g. HTTP/API) per specs‚Äîthird-party push notifications out of MVP scope
- Local: Docker Compose (Postgres + Temporal); production: GCP (see `specs/000-epic-overview`)

## Project Structure

```text
cmd/agent/              # agent binary (composition + long-running agent; not the future public API binary)
cmd/worker/             # Temporal worker: config dial, register each module‚Äôs workflows
cmd/migrate/            # SQL migrations CLI
cmd/retention/          # retention CLI (when used)
# cmd/api/              # add when product HTTP API exists; thin composition like omg-bo cmd/api (Group ‚Üí NewHTTPHandler)
internal/domain/        # shared domain types (e.g. Job)
internal/config/        # env keys + typed loaders only; feature code must not os.Getenv shared knobs
internal/platform/pgsql/ # GORM Postgres + pool; GormGetter; integration migration tests
internal/collectors/    # Collector contract + sources + schema/ (module DTOs at collectors root, not under handlers/)
internal/collectors/handlers/debughttp/  # dev-only HTTP (omg-bo-style handler layout)
internal/jobs/          # jobs module: contract, schema/, impl/, storage/, workflows/ as needed
internal/llm/           # contract, providers, mock/, utils/ ‚Äî no loose helpers at module root
internal/pipeline/      # contract, stage types at root; stage impl in utils/; impl/ if needed
internal/reference/     # optional demos
tests/integration/      # optional; `integration` build tag
migrations/             # SQL migration files
```

**Collectors `schema/`**: module-local DTOs (**`internal/collectors/schema/`** only ‚Äî same level as `contract.go`, `handlers/`, `bootstrap/`). Do **not** nest `schema/` under `handlers/debughttp` or other adapters.

**Debug HTTP today**: `internal/collectors/handlers/debughttp/` is **not** the product API. Layout matches **omg-bo** handlers (stdlib `net/http` instead of Gin): **`handler.go`** with **`NewHTTPHandler(...)`** and **`registerRoutes()`**; **one `.go` file per route**; shared **`helpers.go`** / **`response.go`**. JSON request types for debug POST live in **`internal/collectors/schema/`** (imported by handlers). Wire from composition roots like omg-bo ‚Üí handlers: **`cmd/agent`** ‚Üí **`debughttp.NewHTTPHandler(...)`**. When **`cmd/api`** exists, product routes live there with the same pattern. One-line package comment on `debughttp` stating dev-only.

**Module layout (non-negotiable for feature code)**:

- **`contract.go`** (module root) ‚Äî exported interfaces only.
- **`impl/`** ‚Äî application service / use cases (folder name is **`impl`**, not `service`). Wire depends on `contract` + `storage` + other modules‚Äô contracts.
- **`storage/`** ‚Äî persistence only; this name only (**no** `repository/`).
- **`schema/`** ‚Äî request/response DTOs, handler/workflow payload types, module-local errors (same role as `omg-bo/internal/<feature>/schema`; no shared ‚Äúglobal schema‚Äù repo ‚Äî keep types inside the module).
- **`handlers/`** ‚Äî **omg-bo style**: one file per route/handler, plus **`handler.go`** with `registerRoutes()` (or equivalent) so the full route list is obvious at a glance; shared `helpers.go` / `response.go` only when small.
- **`workflows/`** ‚Äî **omg-api style**: type embedding the worker registrar, `New...` constructor that **explicitly** calls `RegisterWorkflow` for each workflow (readable inventory); `activities/` for activity structs and methods.
- **`utils/`** ‚Äî small shared helpers for that module only; **not** fat domain logic (that belongs in `impl/` or `pipeline/utils/` as already specified).

**Modules**: do not park bulk helpers at the module root. **Temporal** connection lives in `internal/config`; workflow/activity code under `internal/<feature>/workflows/`. See `.specify/memory/constitution.md` for the folder table.

## Testing

- **Unit**: `*_test.go` next to the code, **same package** as the implementation (idiomatic Go).
- **Integration**: `//go:build integration`; run `make test-integration` or `go test -tags=integration ./...` (needs env such as `JOBHOUND_DATABASE_URL` for DB tests, `JOBHOUND_TEMPORAL_ADDRESS` + running worker for Temporal integration tests where applicable).
- Do not rely on `export_test.go` or external `tests/unit/...` trees for ordinary package tests.

## Commands

- `make build` ‚Äî compile `./cmd/agent` to `bin/agent` and `./cmd/worker` to `bin/worker`
- `make run` ‚Äî build and run agent
- `make run-worker` ‚Äî build and run Temporal worker (`JOBHOUND_TEMPORAL_ADDRESS` required)
- `make test` ‚Äî `go test ./...` (excludes `integration`-tagged tests)
- `make test-integration` ‚Äî `go test -tags=integration ./...`
- `make fmt` / `make vet` / `make tidy`

## Code Style

- Go 1.24 conventions; interfaces on module boundaries in `internal/<feature>/contract.go` (or split files); persistence only under `internal/<feature>/storage`
- No secrets or real `.env` in git ‚Äî document `JOBHOUND_*` names in `specs/*/contracts/environment.md`, `README.md`, and `internal/config` (do not duplicate long env lists in the Makefile)
- **Config**: all shared `JOBHOUND_*` (and other app) env names and parsing live in `internal/config`; `cmd/*` loads and passes structs into `internal/*`
- Table-driven tests where behavior branches; keep `main` / `cmd` **thin** ‚Äî composition only, no business rules
- **Comments**: prefer clear names and structure over comment walls. Do not add large banner comments or redundant docblocks on every method; document **non-obvious** invariants, edge cases, or public API where `godoc` matters. If the code is obvious, leave it uncommented

